  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "General Manager – Beach Club",
  "description": "<ul><li>Oversee and take full responsibility for the daily operations of the beach club, including Front of House (FOH) and Back of House (BOH).</li><li>Ensure operations align with the company’s brand standards, service quality, and business goals.</li><li>Drive revenue growth and ensure overall profitability.</li><li>Control food, beverage, and labour costs, ensuring spending stays within approved budgets.</li><li>Ensure full compliance with food safety, hygiene, and regulatory requirements.</li><li>Maintain high levels of customer satisfaction and continuously improve the guest experience.</li><li>Plan and manage manpower and staffing to ensure smooth operations and high productivity.</li><li>Work closely with Marketing and Finance on business proposals, promotions, and campaigns.</li><li>Lead and manage projects such as new outlet openings, renovations, or new concept launches.</li><li>Manage and negotiate contracts with suppliers and vendors.</li><li>Implement strategies to reduce staff turnover and build a stable, motivated team.</li><li>Analyse operational and financial performance to identify issues and implement solutions.</li><li>Develop and execute marketing and sales strategies to increase revenue.</li><li>Identify areas for improvement in operations, processes, and overall performance.</li><li>Collaborate with the Executive / Head Chef on menu planning, seasonal offerings, and food quality standards.</li><li>Set clear, achievable performance goals for Operations Managers and Outlet Managers.</li><li>Stay informed on market trends and changing customer expectations.</li><li>Foster a positive work culture that supports staff development and teamwork.</li><li>Build and lead a team that reflects and supports the company’s vision and values.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 4,
